<BaseLayout title="How to Buy Crypto with Fiat — Complete P2P Trading Guide - 1H Crypto" lang="en" description="From bank account to holding USDT, step-by-step guide on how to safely and cheaply buy cryptocurrency without a foreign bank account." activeNav="learn">
<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
  <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] text-sm mb-2">
    <a href="/en/learn/" class="text-primary hover:underline">← Back to Learning Center</a>
  </p>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">How to Buy Crypto with Fiat — Complete P2P Trading Guide</h1>
  <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] text-sm mb-8">January 2026 · 8 min read</p>

  <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
    <p class="text-lg text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">For Chinese users, "how to turn RMB into USDT" is the first threshold to entering the crypto world. This article explains the complete P2P (peer-to-peer) crypto buying process clearly.</p>

    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/30 mb-8">
      <p class="text-amber-400 text-sm font-medium">⚠️ Risk Warning</p>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] text-sm mt-1">P2P trading involves bank account risks, card freezing, etc. This article is for educational reference only and does not constitute financial advice. Please understand local laws and regulations before operating.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-10 mb-4">What is P2P?</h2>
    <p>P2P (Peer-to-Peer) means "person-to-person" trading — you use the exchange's escrow platform to directly buy USDT (or USDC) from other users with fiat currency. Funds and coins don't pass through the exchange's "fund pool" — the platform acts as the <strong>escrow agent</strong>.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-10 mb-4">Recommended Platform Comparison</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)]">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-semibold">Platform</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-semibold">Supported Payments</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-semibold">Fees</th>
            <th class="py-3 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-semibold">Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)]">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium">Binance P2P</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Alipay, WeChat Pay, Bank Card</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">0% (merchants add spread)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Best liquidity, most merchants</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)]">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium">OKX P2P</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Alipay, WeChat Pay, Bank Card</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">0% (merchants add spread)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Good Chinese UI, strict KYC</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-color)]">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium">Gate.io P2P</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Bank Card, WeChat Pay</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">0% (merchants add spread)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">More coins, average liquidity</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-10 mb-4">Binance P2P Coin Buying: Complete Steps</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3">
      <li><strong>Register and complete KYC</strong>: Register on Binance with phone/email, upload ID for identity verification.</li>
      <li><strong>Enter P2P page</strong>: Click "Buy Crypto" → "P2P Trading" on App homepage.</li>
      <li><strong>Filter merchants</strong>: Select USDT, set filter to "Alipay/WeChat Pay", merchant verification level to "Verified Merchant", completed orders > 500.</li>
      <li><strong>Place order</strong>: Enter purchase amount, click "Buy USDT". System will escrow the funds on the platform.</li>
      <li><strong>Make payment</strong>: Transfer according to the payment info provided by the merchant, within <strong>15 minutes</strong>. <strong>Do NOT write</strong> words like "Bitcoin" "USDT" in the remarks, only write pure number remarks (if merchant requires).</li>
      <li><strong>Confirm receipt</strong>: After the merchant confirms receipt of funds, the platform will release USDT to your spot wallet.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-10 mb-4">7 Iron Rules to Reduce Card Freezing Risk</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Only trade with <strong>platform-verified merchants</strong>, don't transfer privately.</li>
      <li>Single transaction amount shouldn't be too large, recommend < ¥10,000.</li>
      <li>Use a dedicated card: prepare a <strong>seldom-used bank card</strong> specifically for P2P receipts, transfer funds to main card through a "transit card".</li>
      <li>After receiving funds, <strong>don't withdraw immediately</strong>, let it sit on the exchange for at least 24 hours.</li>
      <li>Avoid large transactions during nighttime (22:00-6:00), when bank risk control systems are most sensitive.</li>
      <li>If a merchant asks for "split transfers", refuse — this is usually money laundering behavior.</li>
      <li>Keep all transaction screenshots and chat records as appeal materials in case your bank card gets frozen.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-10 mb-4">What After Buying USDT?</h2>
    <p>After getting USDT, you have several choices:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
      <li><strong>Hold USDT</strong>: Wait for the right timing to buy BTC/ETH.</li>
      <li><strong>Withdraw to hardware wallet</strong>: If amount is large, withdraw from exchange to your own hardware wallet (test with small amount first).</li>
      <li><strong>Participate in DeFi</strong>: Transfer USDT/ETH to wallets like MetaMask, participate in decentralized trading or staking (high risk).</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-8 p-5 rounded-xl bg-[var(--bg-secondary)] border border-[var(--border-color)]">
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-1">🤝 Affiliate Recommendation</p>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] text-sm">Register on Binance and buy via P2P, using the following referral link gets you a fee discount:</p>
      <a href="https://www.binance.com/en/register?ref=CPA_00ZIV33RO4" class="inline-block mt-2 px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">Register Binance (Referral Link) →</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-10 mb-4">Summary</h2>
    <p>P2P is currently the main fiat on-ramp for Chinese users, but also the highest-risk segment. Choose large platforms, verified merchants, dedicated cards, and small fragmented transactions — if you can follow these four rules, risk can be controlled within an acceptable range.</p>
  </div>

